The Western Cape Education Department says it will be releasing a final policy on gender identity and sexual orientation in public schools by the end of the year. eNCA reporter Ayesha Ismail spoke to some queer pupils about their experiences at school. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - A recent social media post regarding a boy wearing a dress to a Cape Town school has once again shone the spotlight on the rights of the LGBTQIA community. Several comments on the post vilified the pupil's choice. READ: School uniforms | Call for flexible dress codes The Western Cape Education Department says it will be releasing its final policy document by the end of this year on gender identity and sexual orientation in public schools. The department says it's in support of the rights of all pupils regardless of sexual orientation. * eNCA's Ayesha Ismail spoke to some queer pupils about their experiences at school. Alison Gray, the deputy principal of Westerford High School in Cape Town, spoke with eNCA's Sally Burdett about the school's policy on gender inclusion. Courtesy of #DStv403